article.headline: Utah 74, Texas St. 69
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas -- Jarred Dubois had 21 points and Jason Washburn added 18 to lead Utah over Texas State 74-69 Friday night. Jordan Loveridge added 15 points and eight rebounds for Utah (5-2). Joel Wright had 17 points and 11 rebounds to lead Texas State (3-4). Vonn Jones added 16 points, and Matt Staff had 16 points and 10 rebounds. The Bobcats hit a pair of 3-pointers in the final minute, but foul trouble had allowed the Utes to pull away earlier. Utah took a 62-55 lead when Wright went to the bench following his fourth foul with seven minutes left in the game. With Wright out, Loveridge had two offensive rebounds that led to a pair of layups by Dubois. The Utes were 14 for 19 on free throws in the second half in what had been a close game.
